BlueCrest Capital Management Ltd Invests $133,000 in Mueller Water Products (MWA)

					Posted by Stanley Muller on Jul 24th, 2017 // No Comments 



BlueCrest Capital Management Ltd bought a new position in  Mueller Water Products (NYSE:MWA) during the first quarter, according to its most recent 13F filing with the SEC. The institutional investor  bought 11,214 shares of the industrial products company’s stock, valued at approximately $133,000. 
Several other institutional investors have also modified their holdings of the company. First Manhattan Co. raised its position in shares of  Mueller Water Products by 4.6% in the first quarter. First Manhattan Co. now owns 369,848 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $4,641,000 after buying an additional 16,396 shares during the period.  Americafirst Capital Management LLC purchased a new position in  Mueller Water Products during the first quarter valued at about $176,000.  Contravisory Investment Management Inc. purchased a new position in  Mueller Water Products during the first quarter valued at about $164,000.  USA Financial Portformulas Corp bought a new stake in  Mueller Water Products during the fourth quarter valued at $237,000.  Finally, Norges Bank bought a new stake in  Mueller Water Products during the fourth quarter valued at $51,312,000. Institutional investors own  87.36% of the company’s stock. 


 Get Mueller Water Products alerts:



Shares of Mueller Water Products (NYSE:MWA) opened at 11.50 on Monday. Mueller Water Products has a 52 week low of $10.45 and a 52 week high of $14.20. The company’s 50 day moving average is $11.43 and its 200-day moving average is $12.03. The stock has a market capitalization of $1.83 billion, a PE ratio of 15.52 and a beta of 1.38. 




Mueller Water Products (NYSE:MWA) last posted its quarterly earnings results on Thursday, April 27th. The industrial products company reported $0.09 EPS for the quarter, hitting the consensus estimate of $0.09. Mueller Water Products had a return on equity of 18.45% and a net margin of 12.45%. The business had revenue of $199.70 million for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $206 million. During the same quarter in the previous year, the firm earned $0.10 EPS. The company’s quarterly revenue was up 1.3% compared to the same quarter last year.  On average, equities analysts predict that  Mueller Water Products will post $0.45 earnings per share for the current year. 
