BlueCrest Capital Management Ltd Takes Position in Ingersoll-Rand PLC (Ireland) (IR)



By Paul Robinson
Company News & Financial Sector
 0 Comments










BlueCrest Capital Management Ltd bought a new position in shares of Ingersoll-Rand PLC (Ireland) (NYSE:IR) during the first quarter, according to its most recent Form 13F filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The firm bought 6,540 shares of the industrial products company’s stock, valued at approximately $532,000. 
Other large investors have also recently made changes to their positions in the company. Scopus Asset Management L.P. purchased a new stake in shares of Ingersoll-Rand PLC (Ireland) during the first quarter worth about $8,132,000. Highbridge Capital Management LLC purchased a new stake in shares of Ingersoll-Rand PLC (Ireland) during the first quarter worth about $269,000. Level Four Advisory Services LLC raised its stake in shares of Ingersoll-Rand PLC (Ireland) by 1.6% in the first quarter. Level Four Advisory Services LLC now owns 7,339 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $600,000 after buying an additional 115 shares in the last quarter. Edmond DE Rothschild Holding S.A. raised its stake in shares of Ingersoll-Rand PLC (Ireland) by 0.3% in the first quarter. Edmond DE Rothschild Holding S.A. now owns 6,169 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $502,000 after buying an additional 17 shares in the last quarter. Finally, HighVista Strategies LLC raised its stake in shares of Ingersoll-Rand PLC (Ireland) by 7.1% in the first quarter. HighVista Strategies LLC now owns 4,500 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $366,000 after buying an additional 300 shares in the last quarter. 82.57% of the stock is currently owned by institutional investors and hedge funds. 
    Get Ingersoll-Rand PLC (Ireland) alerts:    
Ingersoll-Rand PLC (IR) opened at 90.37 on Friday. The firm has a 50-day moving average price of $89.50 and a 200-day moving average price of $82.84. The company has a market capitalization of $23.14 billion, a P/E ratio of 16.42 and a beta of 1.30. Ingersoll-Rand PLC has a 1-year low of $62.40 and a 1-year high of $93.17. 
Ingersoll-Rand PLC (Ireland) (NYSE:IR) last issued its quarterly earnings data on Wednesday, April 26th. The industrial products company reported $0.57 EPS for the quarter, topping the consensus estimate of $0.53 by $0.04. The firm had revenue of $3 billion during the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $2.94 billion. Ingersoll-Rand PLC (Ireland) had a return on equity of 16.44% and a net margin of 10.58%. The company’s quarterly revenue was up 3.7% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same period in the prior year, the business posted $0.50 earnings per share. On average, analysts forecast that Ingersoll-Rand PLC will post $4.51 EPS for the current fiscal year. 
The business also recently disclosed a quarterly dividend, which will be paid on Friday, June 30th. Stockholders of record on Friday, June 9th will be paid a $0.40 dividend. This represents a $1.60 annualized dividend and a dividend yield of 1.77%. The ex-dividend date of this dividend is Wednesday, June 7th. Ingersoll-Rand PLC (Ireland)’s dividend payout ratio (DPR) is presently 29.09%. 







