BlueCrest Capital Management Ltd Takes Position in BPC Acquisition Corp (BERY)

Posted by Dan Jones on Jul 22nd, 2017 // No Comments 

BlueCrest Capital Management Ltd purchased a new position in shares of BPC Acquisition Corp (NYSE:BERY) during the first quarter, according to its most recent 13F filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The fund purchased 4,486 shares of the industrial products company’s stock, valued at approximately $218,000. 
A number of other large investors have also added to or reduced their stakes in the stock. Vanguard Group Inc. increased its stake in shares of BPC Acquisition Corp by 12.0% in the first quarter. Vanguard Group Inc. now owns 10,135,557 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $492,284,000 after buying an additional 1,089,650 shares in the last quarter. Boston Partners increased its stake in shares of BPC Acquisition Corp by 0.8% in the first quarter. Boston Partners now owns 6,935,848 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $336,874,000 after buying an additional 55,837 shares in the last quarter. BlackRock Inc. increased its stake in shares of BPC Acquisition Corp by 20,404.9% in the first quarter. BlackRock Inc. now owns 5,099,577 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $247,685,000 after buying an additional 5,074,707 shares in the last quarter. Bank of Montreal Can increased its stake in shares of BPC Acquisition Corp by 32.0% in the first quarter. Bank of Montreal Can now owns 4,496,662 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $218,403,000 after buying an additional 1,090,024 shares in the last quarter. Finally, FMR LLC increased its stake in shares of BPC Acquisition Corp by 12.8% in the first quarter. FMR LLC now owns 4,206,009 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $204,286,000 after buying an additional 477,381 shares in the last quarter. 98.21% of the stock is currently owned by institutional investors. 




BPC Acquisition Corp (BERY) traded down 0.30% during mid-day trading on Friday, hitting $57.19. 701,714 shares of the stock were exchanged. The firm has a market cap of $7.41 billion, a P/E ratio of 24.81 and a beta of 1.09. BPC Acquisition Corp has a 12-month low of $39.45 and a 12-month high of $58.95. The company has a 50 day moving average of $57.75 and a 200 day moving average of $52.80. 


 Get BPC Acquisition Corp alerts:



BPC Acquisition Corp (NYSE:BERY) last posted its quarterly earnings data on Wednesday, May 3rd. The industrial products company reported $0.79 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, topping the consensus estimate of $0.67 by $0.12. BPC Acquisition Corp had a return on equity of 110.06% and a net margin of 4.50%. The company had revenue of $1.81 billion for the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $1.79 billion. During the same period in the previous year, the business earned $0.58 EPS. BPC Acquisition Corp’s revenue for the quarter was up 11.9% compared to the same quarter last year. On average, equities analysts anticipate that BPC Acquisition Corp will post $2.91 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. 
