US Bancorp DE Has $37.30 Million Position in Donaldson Company, Inc. (DCI)


					Posted by Chloe McGuire on Jul 21st, 2017 // No Comments




US Bancorp DE cut its stake in shares of  Donaldson Company, Inc. (NYSE:DCI) by 1.8% during the second quarter, according to its most recent Form 13F filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The firm owned 819,048 shares of the industrial products company’s stock after selling 15,118 shares during the period. US Bancorp DE owned about 0.62% of Donaldson worth $37,299,000 at the end of the most recent quarter. 
Other hedge funds and other institutional investors have also recently made changes to their positions in the company. Mckinley Capital Management LLC Delaware bought a new position in  Donaldson during the first quarter worth approximately $202,000.  AQR Capital Management LLC bought a new position in  Donaldson during the fourth quarter worth approximately $791,000.  Louisiana State Employees Retirement System increased its position in  Donaldson by 1.8% in the first quarter. Louisiana State Employees Retirement System now owns 33,300 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $1,516,000 after buying an additional 600 shares in the last quarter.  Mountain Pacific Investment Advisers Inc. ID increased its position in  Donaldson by 4.3% in the first quarter. Mountain Pacific Investment Advisers Inc. ID now owns 650,927 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $29,630,000 after buying an additional 26,901 shares in the last quarter.  Finally, Confluence Investment Management LLC increased its position in  Donaldson by 5.4% in the first quarter. Confluence Investment Management LLC now owns 327,359 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $14,901,000 after buying an additional 16,723 shares in the last quarter. 78.77% of the stock is owned by hedge funds and other institutional investors. 


 Get Donaldson Company Inc. alerts:



Donaldson Company, Inc. (NYSE DCI) traded down 0.51% during trading on Friday, reaching $46.93. The company’s stock had a trading volume of 50,794 shares. Donaldson Company, Inc. has a 52-week low of $34.95 and a 52-week high of $48.91. The stock’s 50-day moving average is $46.03 and its 200 day moving average is $44.82. The firm has a market capitalization of $6.15 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 27.93 and a beta of 1.21. 





Donaldson (NYSE:DCI) last issued its quarterly earnings data on Thursday, June 1st. The industrial products company reported $0.45 earnings per share for the quarter, beating the Zacks’ consensus estimate of $0.44 by $0.01. Donaldson had a return on equity of 28.12% and a net margin of 9.72%. The business had revenue of $608.20 million for the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $580.44 million. During the same period last year, the business earned $0.43 EPS. The firm’s revenue was up 6.5% compared to the same quarter last year.  On average, analysts predict that  Donaldson Company, Inc. will post ($0.38) EPS for the current fiscal year. 
The firm also recently announced a quarterly dividend, which was paid on Wednesday, June 28th. Shareholders of record on Monday, June 12th were issued a $0.175 dividend. This represents a $0.70 dividend on an annualized basis and a yield of 1.48%. The ex-dividend date  was Thursday, June 8th. Donaldson’s dividend payout ratio (DPR) is currently 41.92%. 
